To save to localStorage, we use the setItem() method. Here's an example of how to save a key-value pair:

localStorage.setItem("key", "value");

To read back from localStorage, we use the getItem() method. Here's an example of how to retrieve the value stored under the "key" key:

var value = localStorage.getItem("key");

So, in JavaScript, you can save to and read back from localStorage using the setItem() and getItem() methods respectively.
